Policy-relevant questions

Representativeness disclaimer

These analyses are based on responses collected from 5731 caregivers between the dates of April 06, 2020 and July 02, 2020. These caregivers represent a range of voices: 10.19% are Black/African American, 21.17% are LatinX, and 11.46% live at or below 1.5 times the federal poverty line. Proportions/percentages are calculated based on the item-level response rates, not out of the total sample size. The data for these analyses are not weighted.
